VALUES ('2e61037f-9d16-4a6f-9bbf-930b50f724ab', 'Which choice most accurately describes how the text develops its central claim?', 'Archaeologists at site 100149 discovered that pottery shards contained residue of fermented grain, suggesting the community brewed beverages for ritual gatherings rather than daily meals. Layer analysis placed the shards in a ceremonial plaza rather than domestic kitchens, and nearby hearths showed feasting debris concentrated on solstice dates. Chemical tests identified compounds consistent with controlled fermentation but not with large-scale storage for everyday consumption. Nevertheless, subsequent fieldwork revealed limitations that the opening account had treated as settled fact. The team compared the findings with neighboring settlements where grain storage pits dominated the record. That contrast supports the interpretation that brewing here marked special occasions and social bonding. The passage invites readers to connect material evidence with inferred cultural practice without claiming certainty about every recipe', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It outlines a widely held assumption, introduces research challenging its universal application, and clarifies how practitioners should interpret the moderated conclusion as written here throughout overall.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (A). Correct (A). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"B","text":"It describes only the final paragraph''s policy recommendation without accounting for the theoretical setup and evidentiary middle the passage develops before reaching that recommendation here throughout.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"C","text":"It attributes personal ambition to the author instead of analyzing how the text moves from observation to qualified generalization across success