VALUES ('ac119578-f4ca-4b93-adbf-af4db4a7d916', 'Which choice best characterizes the text''s rhetorical structure?', 'Archaeologists at site 100165 discovered that pottery shards contained residue of fermented grain, suggesting the community brewed beverages for ritual gatherings rather than daily meals. Layer analysis placed the shards in a ceremonial plaza rather than domestic kitchens, and nearby hearths showed feasting debris concentrated on solstice dates. Chemical tests identified compounds consistent with controlled fermentation but not with large-scale storage for everyday consumption. The team compared the findings with neighboring settlements where grain storage pits dominated the record. Nevertheless, subsequent fieldwork revealed limitations that the opening account had treated as settled fact. That contrast supports the interpretation that brewing here marked special occasions and social bonding. The passage invites readers to connect material evidence with inferred cultural practice without claiming certainty about every recipe', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It establishes a cause-and-effect claim, supplies seasonal field evidence, and acknowledges limitations before drawing implications in sum in context as written here throughout overall in sum throughout overall in sum in context as","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (A). Correct (A). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"B","text":"It lists technical vocabulary from the opening sentences without showing how those terms support a cumulative argument across the full paragraph from mechanism to outcome in context overall in sum in context as written.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"C","text":"It predicts that the author will publish a memoir, a motivation the passage never discusses or reasonably implies from 